#object-keys <sup>[![Version Badge][2]][1]</sup>

[![Build Status][3]][4] [![dependency status][5]][6]

[![browser support][7]][8]

An Object.keys shim. Uses Object.keys if available.

## Example

```js var keys = require(‘object-keys’); var assert = require(‘assert’); var obj = {

a: true, b: true, c: true

};

assert.equal(keys(obj), [‘a’, ‘b’, ‘c’]); ```

## Source Implementation taken directly from [es5-shim]([9]), with modifications, including from [lodash]([10]).

## Tests Simply clone the repo, npm install, and run npm test
